frameDefinitions: A Speaker succeeds in getting an Addressee to believe or plan to execute the Content the Speaker has in mind.
An Exerter, Action, or Force is capable of exerting or does exert a physical force at a level specified by the target.
A Potential_hindrance or an Agent (via their actions) keeps an Event from taking place, or despite the possibility of prevent the Event, do not do so.
In this frame a Preventing_cause interferes with the ability of a Protagonist to complete an intended Action.

Some Possessor, either a nation, institution, or private individual, controls a Force whose primary functions to defend the Possessor (or, in the case of an institution or individual, some area of land significant to them) and to carry out offensive actions for the Possessor.
The existence of a State_of_affairs is sufficient reason for taking an Action .
frameExamples: At one point, Walter tries to <t>convince</t> his wife that he has had a story accepted by BBC Radio.
Eugenie loved the sea and was a <t>strong</t> swimmer.
Rain <t>prevented</t> the ball game from taking place.
The underwater sequences <t>warrant</t> the price of the admission alone.
listRoleDefinitions: The person that the Speaker seeks to influence to act.
The person who intends through the use of language to get another person to act.
The wish for action on the <fen>Addressee</fen>'s part that the <fen>Speaker</fen> expresses.
A piece of written or spoken material that changes the mind of the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
The general item or items that are the focus of the <fen>Content</fen> of the <fen>Speaker</fen>'s message.
When the <fen>Speaker</fen> suades the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
The location where the Speaker suades the Addressee.
The <fen>Exerter</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Force</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Action</fen> that can or does exert a force of the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Exerter</fen>, <fen>Action</fen>, or <fen>Force</fen> can or does exert its force.
The location where the <fen>Exerter</fen>, <fen>Action</fen>, or <fen>Force</fen> can or does exert its force.
The <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> is the force which keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening, or does not.
The <fen>Event</fen> is prevented from occurring by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen> or the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the sentient being which keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> or <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> or <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Preventing_cause</fen> is the agent or force who keeps the <fen>Protagonist</fen> from completing her or his planned <fen>Action</fen>.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> is the individual or group of individuals who have a planned <fen>Action</fen> which is prevented by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen>
The <fen>Action</fen> is the action or event certain individuals desire to bring about which is prevented by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the thwarting occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the thwarting occurs.
The <fen>Force</fen> is the body of soldiers that acts in military capacity for the <fen>Possessor</fen>. This role is incorporated in each word in this frame.
The <fen>Possessor</fen> is the nation, institution, or individual who possesses and/or controls the <fen>Force</fen>.
An Eventuality or an Entity that is taken to constitute sufficient reason for taking another <fen>Action</fen>.
An <fen>Action</fen> that is taken to be justifiable given the <fen>State_of_Affairs</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>His speech</fex> convinced me to join the Peace Corps.
You haven't convinced me <fex>about that yet</fex>.
Salesmen touted the power <fex>of the engine's motor</fex>.
No one should underestimate the mighty <fex>strength</fex> of the dung beetle.
She gave him a playful, weak <fex>punch</fex> in the arm.
My quads feel particularly weak <fex>after 100 squats</fex>.
Muhammad Ali's force <fex>in the ring</fex> was indisputable.
The American invasion, which drew 26000 American troops against <fex>General Noriega's</fex> army, was the largest US military operation since Vietnam.
<fex>A heavy contact to the opponent 's face</fex> may not merit just a verbal warning
